1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:03,548
Collaboration works best when access has a purpose.

2
00:00:03,548 --> 00:00:07,884
Decide whether someone needs to view, code, review or manage

3
00:00:07,884 --> 00:00:12,219
the project before sharing a canvas or inviting them into

4
00:00:12,219 --> 00:00:13,520
a team workflow.

5
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:18,418
For a team study, agree who owns the codebook, when

6
00:00:18,418 --> 00:00:22,466
coders work independently and how disagreements will be resolved.

7
00:00:22,466 --> 00:00:27,864
Software can show activity; it cannot make those methodological decisions for you.

8
00:00:28,264 --> 00:00:32,566
Open Share from the workspace and use the available access controls.

9
00:00:32,566 --> 00:00:36,476
A share code or link grants access, so send it

10
00:00:36,476 --> 00:00:40,387
through an appropriate channel and revoke or rotate it when

11
00:00:40,387 --> 00:00:41,560
the collaboration ends.

12
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:46,831
Before checking agreement, confirm that every coder worked from the

13
00:00:46,831 --> 00:00:49,754
same definitions and unit of analysis.

14
00:00:49,754 --> 00:00:55,112
A metric cannot rescue an ambiguous codebook or inconsistent passage boundaries.

15
00:00:55,512 --> 00:00:59,877
The intercoder view can calculate agreement from comparable coding work.

16
00:00:59,877 --> 00:01:04,242
Treat the score as a signal: inspect the disagreements, discuss

17
00:01:04,242 --> 00:01:08,607
the reasoning and revise the codebook when the pattern reveals

18
00:01:08,607 --> 00:01:09,480
genuine ambiguity.

19
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:14,272
When coders disagree, return to the passage and its context.

20
00:01:14,272 --> 00:01:18,664
Record the resolution in a memo so the next similar

21
00:01:18,664 --> 00:01:23,056
case is handled consistently and the methods account remains transparent.

22
00:01:23,456 --> 00:01:28,392
A sound collaboration has clear roles, shared definitions, a period

23
00:01:28,392 --> 00:01:32,834
of independent work and a documented discussion of differences.

24
00:01:32,834 --> 00:01:38,264
QualCanvas supports that process; the research team remains responsible for it.
